            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "; otherwise, one of the error codes described in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage/data_types_and_constants"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This function overwrites the entire destination Core Video pixel buffer. If you don't want to copy the entire vImage buffer, you can use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/1399134-vimageconvert_anytoany"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and a converter prepared with "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/1498241-vimageconverter_createforcgtocvi"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The source vImage buffer and the destination pixel buffer must be the same size; otherwise, the operation fails and the function returns "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/1578972-error_codes/kvimagebuffersizemismatch"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For compatibility with Core Video, vImage substitutes gamma 1/1.961 for "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corevideo/kcvimagebuffertransferfunction_itu_r_709_2"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corevideo/kcvimagebuffertransferfunction_smpte_240m_1995"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instead of using the ITU-R BT.709-5 specified transfer function.  If you don't want this substitution to be made, you can manually set the transfer function using "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/1498273-vimagecreatergbcolorspacewithpri"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/1498233-vimagecvimageformat_setcolorspac"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
